I'm Using Kaa Opensource IoT platform to control GPIO of ESP8266. Im using ESP-01 module for this project. Im using this example. Getting error while compiling the code 

[ 93%] Building C object CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/src/kaa_demo.c.obj	/home/sse/Kaa/ESP8266/kaa_gpio_esp8266_example/src/kaa_demo.c:23:40: fatal error: gen/kaa_remote_control_ecf.h: No such file or directory	 #include <gen/kaa_remote_control_ecf.h>	                                        ^	compilation terminated.	CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/build.make:62: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/src/kaa_demo.c.obj' failed	make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/src/kaa_demo.c.obj] Error 1	CMakeFiles/Makefile2:69: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/all' failed	make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/demo_client_s.dir/all] Error 2	Makefile:127: recipe for target 'all' failed	make: *** [all] Error 2

there is a file missing named gen/kaa_remote_control_ecf.h Im not able to locate this file anywhere.

Is there any other way to find this file?

I'm using latest Kaa SDK 0.10.
